## Testing Philosophy

> **Test behavior, not implementation.**

- Write tests that describe *what* the system does, not *how* it does it internally.
- If you can refactor the implementation without changing behavior, the tests should still pass.
- Prefer testing public APIs (function inputs/outputs, HTTP endpoints, rendered UI) over internal methods.
- Tests are documentation -- a new developer should understand the feature by reading its tests.

---

## Test Pyramid

```
         /  E2E  \          ~10% of tests
        /----------\
       / Integration \      ~20% of tests
      /----------------\
     /    Unit Tests     \  ~70% of tests
    /____________________\
```

**Unit tests** are fast, cheap, and catch logic errors early.
**Integration tests** verify that components work together (API + DB, frontend + API).
**E2E tests** verify critical user flows through the full stack.

