## CI/CD Test Pipeline

```yaml
# Pipeline stages (run in order):
# 1. Install dependencies
# 2. Lint + Type check (parallel, fast fail)
# 3. Unit tests (parallel across packages)
# 4. Integration tests (sequential, needs DB service)
# 5. Build (verify production build succeeds)
# 6. E2E tests (needs full stack running -- staging only)
# 7. Coverage report + gate check
```

- Tests run on **every PR** and **every push to main**
- Coverage report posted as PR comment
- **Failing tests block merge** -- no exceptions
- E2E tests run on staging deploy (not on every PR)
- Flaky tests are tracked and fixed within 1 sprint

---

## When to Skip Tests

Tests can be skipped **only** with explicit justification:

| OK to Skip | NOT OK to Skip |
|---|---|
| Pure UI layout (no logic) | Business logic |
| Third-party library wrappers (trust the library) | API endpoints |
| Generated code (Prisma client, GraphQL types) | Auth and authorization |
| One-off scripts that will be deleted | Data transformations |
| Prototype / spike code (must add tests before merge to main) | Error handling |

When skipping, **always** add a comment:
```typescript
// SKIP-TEST: [reason] -- [TASK-XXX or "will add before merge"]
it.skip('should handle edge case', () => { ... });
```

